American Realty Capital REIT auditor resigns without explanation






























 






























  Free Case Evaluation : 877.238.4175 Tap Here To Call Us   







 
Stock Fraud News & Information

Published By Fitapelli | Kurta





           Stock Fraud News & Information         STOCK FRAUD CLAIMS PRODUCTS PRESS     












Published on: February 3, 2015
American Realty Capital REIT auditor resigns without explanation

By Fitapelli Kurta






 



According to a recent article in InvestmentNews, Grant Thornton, one of the world’s leading auditing firms, has resigned from eight Real Estate Investment Trusts (REITs) all of which are managed by Nicholas Schorsch, including American Realty Capital. Grant Thornton gave no reason or explanation for this resignations.
Grant Thornton previously audited 16 American Realty Capital investment programs. Among those REITs which Grant Thornton resigned from last week include: ARC – Retail Centers of America, Inc., ARC – Retail Centers of America II, Inc., ARC Daly Net Asset Value Trust, Inc., ARC Healthcare Trust II, Inc. ARC Healthcare Trust II, Inc. ARC New York City REIT, Inc. and ARC Realty Finance Trust, Inc.
American Realty Capital has been in the spotlight, though not in the best light, since October 2014 when it was discovered that America Realty Capital Properties, Inc. had made a $23 million accounting error that was intentionally left uncorrected during the first half of 2014. Since then Nicholas Schorsch has resigned as Chairman of American Realty Capital Properties and the sales of American Realty Capital REITs have significantly slowed, as many broker-dealers suspended offering the product. Deloitte Touche will become the new internal auditor to all ARC-sponsored programs.
A lawsuit is currently pending, alleging that American Realty Capital violated federal securities laws and made false and misleading statements by “misrepresenting the company’s business and prospects and engaged in a scheme to deceive the market and a course of conduct that artificially inflated prices of American Realty securities.”
If you or someone you know has lost money investing through ARC – Retail Centers of America, Inc., ARC – Retail Centers of America II, Inc., ARC Daly Net Asset Value Trust, Inc., ARC Healthcare Trust II, Inc. ARC Healthcare Trust II, Inc. ARC New York City REIT, Inc. and ARC Realty Finance Trust, Inc. or any other REIT through American Realty Properties, you may be entitled to full recovery of your losses.
REITs like ARC – Retail Centers of America, Inc., ARC – Retail Centers of America II, Inc., ARC Daly Net Asset Value Trust, Inc., ARC Healthcare Trust II, Inc. ARC Healthcare Trust II, Inc. ARC New York City REIT, Inc. and ARC Realty Finance Trust, Inc. are extremely risky, and broker-dealers who offer these investments have a duty to warn investors of those risks and to only offer investments which are suitable to each investor’s needs.
The law offers a path of recovery to investors who have fallen victim to broker misconduct and who have lost money investing in speculative investments like REITs by way of arbitration through the Financial Industry Regulatory Authority (FINRA). Fitapelli Kurta exclusively arbitrates cases on behalf of investors nationwide. Out law firm has recovered millions on behalf of investors and we will work fervently to defend your claim.
Call 212-658-1502 now to speak directly to an attorney. Our consultations are always free and all cases are taken on a contingency fee basis.
Time to file a claim with FINRA is limited, so do not delay. Call now.
 














